<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05015d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05015d">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05015d"> 15(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> litter of kittens</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">All the good men had gone wrong, and God repented that he had made them. He appears to have been utterly baffled by his own creatures. He might have called a few priests &rdquo;home,&rdquo; and sent a few schoolmasters in their places. Something might have been attempted. Surely the being who said &rdquo;Let there be light! and there was light,&rdquo; could as easily have said, &rdquo;Let all men be good, or decent!&rdquo; and they would have been so. But God&apos;s ways are not as our ways. He resolved to drown his children like a <mark>litter of kittens</mark>. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) 52f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
